y well (positive)\n- solves problems extremely well (positive)\n- takes responsibility seriously (positive)\n- regarded as a know-it-all (negative)\n- has a hot temper (negative)\n\nWe need to weigh for long-distance pilot: reliability, technical competence, calm under pressure, decision-making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nCandidate A: strong technical and leadership, but show-off and not open to new ideas could affect crew morale and adaptability. No mention of calmness under pressure.\n\nCandidate B: extremely reliable, calm in crisis, good weather assessment, but poor teamwork (nasty remarks) and weak memory for numbers (could affect calculations). No mention of decision speed.\n\nCandidate C: good decision speed, conscientious, tech-savvy, creates positive crew atmosphere, but egocentric, poor communication, not willing to further education. However positive crew atmosphere may offset some.\n\nCandidate D: strong problem solving, responsibility, concentration, handles unexpected events, but hot temper and know-it-all attitude could harm crew cooperation. No explicit calmness under pressure, but problem solving suggests competence.\n\nWe need to decide best overall. Likely Candidate C seems balanced: good decision-making, crew atmosphere, technical, conscientious. Negatives: egocentric, communication difficulty, not eager to learn. But crew atmosphere is important for long flights. Candidate B reliability is high but teamwork is poor. Candidate A leadership but not open to new ideas. Candidate D hot temper.\n\nThus I might lean toward Candidate C. But we should ask other agents if they have any missing positive attributes for candidates we are uncertain about, e.g., does anyone have info on Candidate A's calmness under pressure? Or Candidate D's calmness? Or Candidate B's teamwork? We can ask Agent 1 or 3.\n\nWe can ask Agent 1: \"Do you have any information about Candidate A's ability to stay calm under pressure or handle stress?\" Also ask about Candidate D's temperament in crew context.\n\nWe should produce public message with reasoning and ask targeted questions.\n\nWe also need to include vote in metadata. I think vote for Candidate C.\n\nProceed."}
