blem solving, responsibility, know-it-all, hot temper. No calmness info, no teamwork.\n\nWe need to choose best for long-distance pilot. Key criteria: reliability, technical competence, calm under pressure, decision-making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nReliability: B (100% reliable). Others not mentioned.\n\nCalm under pressure: B (keeps calm in crisis). Others unknown.\n\nTechnical competence: A (spatial vision, complex connections), C (understands complicated tech), B (weather assessment), D (problem solving). All decent.\n\nDecision-making: C (quick correct decisions), A (anticipates dangerous situations), D (problem solving), B (no data).\n\nTeamwork/communication: A (leadership), B (nasty remarks), C (difficulty communicating), D (hot temper). Only A has leadership, but also negative perception. No explicit positive teamwork for any.\n\nProfessional development: A not open to new ideas, B no data, C not willing to further education, D no data.\n\nThus B stands out for reliability and calmness, which are critical for safety. The teamwork issue is serious, but we have no positive teamwork for any candidate. So we might still vote B, acknowledging the risk.\n\nWe could also ask if any agent has any positive teamwork info for any candidate, but they all said no. So we proceed.\n\nThus vote Candidate B.\n\nNow produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE: Summarize that we have no info on A calmness, D crew behavior, B teamwork, and give our assessment leaning to B, and maybe ask if anyone has any positive teamwork info for any candidate. Provide reasoning.\n\nThen METADATA_JSON with vote B.\n\nProceed."}
